msgstr "DOST proyek NOAH mengadopsi teknologi Indonesia untuk mitigasi bencana"

# b0cbacdc57e84553b32dba6a1b3519b9
#: ../../source/general/news.rst:69
msgid ""
"The Department of Science and Technology’s (DOST) Project NOAH (Nationwide "
"Operational Assessment of Hazards) is adopting the disaster mitigating "
"technology called |project_name| from Indonesia. |project_name| is an "
"acronym for Indonesia Scenario Assessment for Emergency."
msgstr "Department of Science and Technology’s (DOST) Proyek NOAH (Nationwide Operational Assessment of Hazards) mengadopsi teknologi mtigasi bencana yang bernama |project_name| dari Indonesia. |project_name| adalah singkatan untuk Indonesia Scenario Assessment for Emergency."

# 7d012e2f84d547bb9023066916c5f0db
#: ../../source/general/news.rst:74
msgid ""
"It is an open source technology, which means it is free, readily accessed "
"from the internet and may be modified by users. With this technology, data "
"coming from weather scientists, local government units and communities are "
"gathered and consolidated to provide accurate information on future disaster"
" events. NOAH adopted Indonesias’s InaSAFE as it has a lot in common with "
"the Philippines, especially in topography and natural hazards. This was "
"disclosed during the multi-stakeholder assembly titled “Enhancing Community "
"Resilience Through the Use of New Technology” conducted by Project NOAH."
msgstr "Hal ini adalah teknologi open source, yang berarti gratis, mudah diakses dari internet dan mungkin dimodifikasi oleh pengguna. Dengan teknologi ini, data yang berasal dari para ilmuwan cuaca, unit pemerintah daerah, dan komunitas dikumpulkan dan dikonsolidasikan untuk memberikan informasi akurat pada peristiwa bencana yang akan datang. NOAH mengadopsi InaSAFE Indonesia yang memiliki berbagai banyak kesamaan dengan Filipina, khususnya pada topografi dan bencana alamnya. Hal ini diungkapkan saat perakitan multi-pemangku kepentingan yang berjudul “Meningkatkan Ketahanan Masyarakat melalui Penggunaan Teknologi Baru“ yang dilakukan oleh Proyek NOAH."

# 212e3f4aeb7f49a0828974464c3be7c8
#: ../../source/general/news.rst:84
msgid ""
"Abigail Baca, disaster and risk management officer of the World Bank East "
"Asia and Pacific Region said that |project_name| proved effective during the"
" recent floods in Jakarta and Indonesia; thus, they arrived at a conclusion "
"that it can be likewise applied in the Philippines."
msgstr "Abigail Baca, pejabat manajemen risiko dan bencana dari World Bank Wilayah Asia Timur dan Pasifik mengungkapkan bahwa |project_name| terbukti efektif saat banjir di Jakarta dan Indonesia; dengan demikian, mereka berangkat dari kesimpulan bahwa hal itu dapat juga diaplikasikan di Filipina."

# f7f1df93d50d4522a44937ef59fbdbc1
#: ../../source/general/news.rst:89
msgid ""
"Dr. Alfredo Francisco Mahar Lagmay of Project NOAH disclosed that InaSAFE "
"will be integrated into Project NOAH to supplement existing technologies "
"used to mitigate, if not totally prevent, massive destruction caused by "
"strong typhoons similar to Sendong in 2011and Pablo in December 2012."
msgstr "Dr. Alfredo Francisco Mahar Lagmay Proyek NOAH mengungkapkan bahwa InaSAFE akan diintegrasika ke dalam Proyek NOAH untuk melengkapi teknologi yang ada digunakan untuk mitigasi, jika tidak benar-benar mencegah, kerusakan besar yang disebabkan oleh topan yang kuat seperti Sendong pada 2011 dan Pablo pada Desember 2012."

# 4d197e130c4f4d72a04c4a7f2b3707d9
#: ../../source/general/news.rst:94
msgid ""
"During his presentation, Dr. Lagmay said, “It is important to develop "
"information tools that will help centralize risk information at the NOAH "
"website and make them available to a wider community.” Since its launch in "
"July 2012 in Marikina City, Project NOAH has continuously upgraded and "
"strengthened its capability through the installation of various weather "
"forecasting equipment in various disaster-prone areas in the country. Among "
"these are the Hydromet water level sensors and Doppler radars used to "
"measure the amount of rainfall in a specific area."
msgstr "Selama presentasinya, Dr. Lagmay berkata, “Hal ini sangat penting untuk mengembangkan alat informasi yang akan membantu pemusatan informasi risiko di website NOAH dan akan disediakan untuk masyarakat luas.”  Sejak diluncurkan pada Juli 2012 di  Kota Marinka. Proyek NOAH telah terus ditingkatkan dan dikuatkan kemampuan melalui pemasangan berbagai jenis peralatan perkiraan cuaca di berbagai wilayah rawan bencana Filipina. Diantaranya adalah sensor level air Hydromet dan radar Doppler digunakan untuk mengukur jumlah curah hujan di area tertentu."

# d8ccf91896c247ce8e82707e523be8f3
#: ../../source/general/news.rst:103
msgid ""
"To date, there are 525 Hydromet sensors installed in different river "
"systems, including those in Tullahan River, Marikina River and San Juan "
"River in Metro Manila. Likewise, the Project NOAH team has put up billboards"
" in Pampanga showing flood maps to inform residents of the high-risk areas "
"in their communities."
msgstr "Untuk saat ini, ada 525 sensor Hydromet yang dipasang di sistem sungai yang berbeda, termasuk di Sungai Tullahan, Sungai Marikina, dan Sungai San Juan di Metro Manila. Demikian juga, tim Proyek NOAH telah memasang baliho di Pampanga yang menunjukkan peta banjir untuk informasi penduduk daerah berisiko tinggi di masyarakat mereka."

# 6a80d62e098e4f4e95a6383feef7ffc6
#: ../../source/general/news.rst:109
msgid ""
"Further, Dr. Enrico C. Paringit, project leader of NOAH’s DREAM LiDAR "
"(Disaster Risk and Exposure Assessment for Mitigation-Light Detection and "
"Ranging) said, “ Since November 2012, we were able to do three-dimensional "
"or 3D mapping of the Pampanga river basin, Agno River, Cagayan de Oro and "
"Iligan. By the end of May this year, 3D mapping for Iloilo will be complete "
"and next in line is the Panay river basin.”"
msgstr "Selanjutnya, Dr. Enrico C. Paringit, ketua proyek NOAH DREAM LiDAR  (Disaster Risk and Exposure Assessment for Mitigation-Light Detection and Ranging) mengatakan, “Sejak November 2012, kami mampu melakukan pemetaan 3D atau tiga dimensi pada DAS Pampanga, Sungai Agno, Cagayan de Oro dan Iligan. Pada akhir Mei tahun ini, pemetaan 3D untuk Iloilo akan dilengkapi dan selanjutnya di sepanjang DAS Panay.”"

